Johnson Okafor The nation’s stock market on Tuesday sustained positive sentiment to the sixth consecutive trading session as the market capitalisation gained N46bn. The key market performance indicators, the Nigerian Stock Exchange All Share Index and market capitalisation, rose by 0.34 per cent following investors’ sustained optimism on undervalued stocks. The market breadth closed positive as gainers at the close of trading session was 27 while losers were nine. The All-Share Index rose by 86.82 basis points or 0.34 per cent to close at 25,413.95 as against 25,327.13 recorded the previous day while market capitalisation of equities appreciated by N46bn or 0.34 per cent to close higher at N13.26tn from N13.21tn. Meanwhile, a turnover of 1.07 billion shares in 3,221 deals was recorded in the day’s trading. Real estate development sub-sector was the most active (measured by turnover volume), with 947.74m shares exchanged by investors in 21 deals. Volume in the sub-sector was driven by activities in the shares of UAC Property Development Company Plc. The premium sub-sector was boosted by the activities in the shares of Access Bank Plc and Zenith Bank Plc, with a turnover of 48.04 million shares in 1,043 deals. Further analysis of the day’s trading showed that Livestock Feeds Plc led the gainers’ table with 10 per cent to close at 66 kobo per share while Eterna Oil Plc followed with 9.47 per cent to close at N2.08 per share. Jaiz Bank Plc appreciated by 8.93 per cent to close at 61 Kobo per share. On the other hand, Wapic Insurance Plc led the losers’ chart with a drop of 5.71 per cent to close at 33 kobo per share. UBN Plc followed with a loss of 5.66 per cent to close at N5.00 per share while PZ Cussons Plc dropped by 2.38 per cent to close at N4.10 per share. Copyright PUNCH.
